          </head>
          <p>The Grolier Club, New York, presented an exhibition of Blakeâ€™s book illustrations from 25 March
through the end of May. All works were from the collection of Robert N. Essick. The exhibit centered on the
engraved book illustrations designed and executed by Blake, but also included reproductive graphics, a small
selection of early facsimiles of the illuminated books, and the recently rediscovered copy h of 
<hi rend="i">Songs of Innocence and of Experience.</hi> The exhibition was not open to the public.</p>
